s, it is a power. The simplicity of gentleness is misleading. It is an active passivity that may become an extraordinary force of symbolic resistance and, as such, become central to both ethics and politics. Gentleness is a force of secret life-giving transformation linked to what the ancients called potentiality.In our day, gentleness is sold to us under its related form of diluted mawkishness. By infantilizing it our era denies it. This is how we try to overcome the high demands of its subtlety-no longer by fighting it, but by enfeebling it. Language itself is therefore perverted: what our society intends to give the human beings that it crushes "gently," it does in the name of the highest values: happiness, truth, security.From listening to those who come to me and confide their despair, I have heard it expressed in every lived experience. I have felt its force of resistance and its intangible magic. In mediating its relation to the world, it appears that its intelligence carries life, saves and amplifies it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aPassivity (Psychology). 0aTenderness (Psychology). 7aPHILOSOPHY / Mind & Body.2bisacsh  aBody.  aGentleness.  aPotential.  aPower.  aPsychoanalysis.1 aMalabou, Catherine.1 aPayne, Katherine.1 aSallé, Vincent.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311072900940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823279623zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823279623423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780823279623.jpg  a978-3-11-072900-9  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deG